-{"id":"br-r37-c1-01","title":"REVIEW: [HIGH] condensation used wrong SCC labeling (source-first instead of sink-first)","description":"fnx.condensation(G) labeled SCCs via the Rust _condensation_raw internal order, which numbered source SCCs first. nx numbers SCCs in strongly_connected_components() order (sinks first). Consequence: C.graph['mapping'], C.nodes[i]['members'], and condensation edges had integer labels flipped relative to networkx, silently breaking downstream code that indexes SCCs by label. Fixed by rebuilding condensation on top of fnx's own strongly_connected_components iterator so labels stay bit-compatible.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: condensation now iterates strongly_connected_components(G) and assigns indices in emission order, matching networkx's convention. Tested on 5-node 2-SCC DAG; mapping, edges, and members all match nx exactly; scc= arg path and empty-graph path also match."}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-02","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] node_connectivity on MultiGraph with parallel edges returned simple-graph value","description":"fnx.node_connectivity(MultiGraph) called into _raw_node_connectivity which collapses parallel edges. On e.g. K3 with extra parallel edges between two pairs, networkx returns min-degree=3 (parallel edges inflate the degree bound) while fnx returned 2 (simple-graph κ=n−1). Fixed by delegating multigraph inputs to networkx to preserve parity. Simple Graph/DiGraph continue to use the Rust fast path.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: node_connectivity now delegates when G.is_multigraph(). Verified on K3-parallel, K3 MG no-parallel, MDG with parallel edges — all match nx."}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-03","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] edge_connectivity returned float and ignored MultiGraph parallel edges","description":"Two related defects in edge_connectivity: (1) simple Graph path returned a float (e.g. 2.0) via the max-flow pipeline while nx returns an int cardinality (2). (2) MultiGraph path collapsed parallel edges: on K3 with extra parallel edges fnx returned 2.0 vs nx's 3. Fixed by coercing int-valued floats to int before returning, and delegating multigraph inputs to networkx.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: MG/MDG delegate to nx; simple Graph path casts integral float back to int. Verified across K3 simple, DG, MG with/without parallel, MDG — all match nx in value and type."}
