 {"id": "franken_networkx-loadcent", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] load_centrality returned betweenness_centrality as a shortcut; Newman's load differs in practice", "description": "fnx.load_centrality's (cutoff=None, weight=None) fast path returned betweenness_centrality(G) directly. While often described as equivalent for unweighted graphs, Newman's load algorithm counts path fractions differently when multiple shortest paths share intermediate nodes — on the karate club graph the two diverged on 18/34 nodes by ~1-5% (node 0: fnx/betweenness=0.4376 vs nx/load=0.4347). Dropped the shortcut and routed every case through _load_centrality_from_source_local, which already mirrors nx._node_betweenness exactly (predecessor-based reverse-BFS accumulation). Verified 0/34 diffs on karate (unweighted and weighted) and on the 4-node MultiGraph test fixture.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T16:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T16:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T16:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Native Newman's load impl via _load_centrality_from_source_local", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
