 {"id": "franken_networkx-louvainquality", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] louvain_communities returned suboptimal partition (Rust missed second-phase aggregation)", "description": "Louvain is a two-phase iterative modularity maximizer — Phase 1 moves nodes between communities; Phase 2 collapses each community to a super-node and re-runs Phase 1; iterate until convergence. The Rust _raw_louvain_communities only did Phase 1 once, yielding a markedly lower-quality partition than nx. On karate_club_graph: fnx returned 2 communities {16, 18} with modularity ~0.4036 for every seed tested, while nx returned 4 communities {4, 6, 10, 14} with modularity ~0.4266-0.4439. Route fnx.louvain_communities through _louvain_impl which delegates to nx.algorithms.community.louvain_communities via _call_networkx_submodule_for_parity so fnx matches nx's partition quality.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T17:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T17:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T17:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate to nx's hierarchical Louvain", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
